# CUDA variant — heavy ML stack for Dockerfile.cuda
# torch cu126 wheels from https://download.pytorch.org/whl/cu126
# Edit versions here, then run: make compile-heavy
#
# Pin rationale:
#   torch/torchaudio 2.9.1+cu126  — Nov 2025, NeMo 2.7.3 needs torch>=2.6.0.
#   nemo-toolkit[asr] 2.7.3       — Apr 2026, adds canary2 prompt formatter.
#   lightning/pytorch-lightning 2.4.0 — NeMo 2.7.3 hard-pins lightning<=2.4.0.
#   huggingface-hub 0.35.3        — last release with symlink->copy fallback (SMB cache).
#   transformers 4.57.3           — qwen-tts hard-pin; within NeMo's ~=4.57.0 tolerance.
#   faster-qwen3-tts 0.2.6        — CUDA-graph-optimized Qwen3-TTS wrapper (MIT).
#
# Known open CVEs (threat-modelled; not exploitable in this app):
#   PYSEC-2026-139 (torch pt2 load): we don't torch.load() untrusted files.
#   GHSA-75m9-98v2-hjpm (PL load_from_checkpoint): we don't call it.
#   GHSA-69w3-r845-3855 / PYSEC-2025-217 (transformers Trainer): we don't train.
